        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 9:08PM CDT by NWS North Platte NE</headline>
        <description>At 908 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hayes Center, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hayes Center, Marengo, and Hayes Center State Wildlife Management
Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
